# 🏥 OT Roster Hub
### Operation Theater Shift & Team Manager

A mobile-friendly web app for hospital staff to manage shifts, view team rosters, and chat in real time — organised by hospital and department.

---

## 📱 Install on Your Phone

OT Roster Hub works like a native app on both iPhone and Android. No App Store needed.

### iPhone (Safari)

1. Open the app URL in **Safari** (must be Safari, not Chrome)
2. Tap the **Share button** at the bottom of the screen — it looks like a box with an arrow pointing up ⬆
3. Scroll down and tap **"Add to Home Screen"**
4. Edit the name if you like, then tap **Add**
5. The app icon now appears on your home screen — tap it to open like any other app

> ⚠️ This only works in Safari on iPhone. If you are using Chrome or another browser, switch to Safari first.

---

### Android (Chrome)

1. Open the app URL in **Chrome**
2. Chrome may automatically show a pop-up banner at the bottom saying **"Add to Home Screen"** — tap it
3. If the banner doesn't appear, tap the **three-dot menu** (⋮) in the top right corner
4. Tap **"Install App"** or **"Add to Home Screen"**
5. Tap **Install** — the app icon appears in your app drawer and home screen

---

## ✨ Features

- 📅 **My Calendar** — add and manage your personal shifts with custom colours and names
- 👥 **Team Roster** — see all shifts for your department in real time
- 💬 **Team Chat** — live group chat shared across all team members
- 🪪 **Members** — see everyone registered in your hospital and department
- 👤 **My Profile** — view your stats, change theme, delete your account
- 🗄 **My Data** — see exactly what data is stored against your account

---

## 🔒 Privacy & Security

- Your data is **isolated by hospital and department** — users from other hospitals or departments cannot see your data
- All data is stored securely in **Google Firebase Firestore**
- Deleting your profile permanently removes all your shifts, messages, and member record

---

## 🌍 Supported Countries & Holidays

The app automatically loads public holidays for your country from an external API. Currently supported:

| Country | Code |
|---|---|
| Australia | AU |
| United States | US |
| United Kingdom | GB |
| Canada | CA |
| New Zealand | NZ |
| Ireland | IE |
| India | IN |
| South Africa | ZA |

---

## 🛠 Built With

- [Firebase Firestore](https://firebase.google.com) — real-time database
- [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com) — styling
- [Font Awesome](https://fontawesome.com) — icons
- [Nager.Date API](https://date.nager.at) — public holidays
- Hosted on [GitHub Pages](https://pages.github.com) — free hosting

---

## 📋 First Time Setup

1. Open the app URL in your browser
2. Enter your **Full Name**, **Position**, **Hospital**, **Department**, and **Country**
3. Tap **Enter the OR**
4. Your profile is created and saved — colleagues at the same hospital and department will see you in Members

> 💡 Tip: Make sure your hospital name and department match **exactly** with your colleagues (same spelling, same capitalisation) so you end up in the same group.

